# Debugging STS2 Context Coach — use Godot logs

When investigating in-game behavior (LLM, shop probe, game state, overlays), **read the game logs early**, not only the C# source.

## Where to look (keep this list for future sessions)

**Game / engine (all mods, including stack traces for failed manifests):**

| What | Path (Windows) |
|------|----------------|
| Current log | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\logs\godot.log` |
| Older sessions | Same folder: `godot2026-*.log` (timestamp in filename) |

**Context Coach–written files (outside `mods/` so STS2 does not treat them as mod manifests):**

| What | Path (Windows) |
|------|----------------|
| Writable root | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\` |
| Telemetry / run folders | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\logs\<run-id>\` (`events.jsonl`, `metadata.json`, `summary.json`; optional `llm/` when `llm_mirror_transcripts_into_run_folder` is true) |
| Active-run pointer | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\logs\active_run.json` |
| LLM transcripts | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\logs\llm\coach-*.json` (when `llm_log_transcripts` is true in `contextcoach.config`) |
| Export ZIPs | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\exports\` |
| Export UI state | `%AppData%\Roaming\SlayTheSpire2\Sts2ContextCoach\logs\export_state.json` |

**Mod folder (install location; only read `Sts2ContextCoach.json`, DLL, `contextcoach.config`, CSV — avoid extra `*.json` here):**

- Typical: `<Steam>\steamapps\common\Slay the Spire 2\mods\Sts2ContextCoach\`

Correlate LLM transcript files with `godot.log` lines `[ContextCoach][LLM] transcript` and `[ContextCoach][LLM] POST` / `ok` / `batch failed`. Match **`corr=`** in the log to `corr` in `events.jsonl` **`llm_coach_batch`** / **`llm_deck_summary`** rows and to the transcript filename suffix (`coach-*-{corr}.json`).

## What to grep

- `[ContextCoach]` — mod lifecycle, scoring mode, snapshot hints
- `[ContextCoach][LLM]` — `schedule`, `batchKey`, `candidates=`, `POST`, `ok`, `batch failed`, `debounce superseded`, `shop LLM row` (includes `shopRootBfs=`, `mode=`)
- In `events.jsonl`, grep `"event_type":"llm_coach_batch"` / `"llm_deck_summary"` for structured outcomes and `transcript_file` basename

## Patterns that have meant real bugs

- **`shopRootBfs=1`** with paths under `MerchantCardHolder*` → wrong shop BFS root (per-slot “Merchant” match), not full `MerchantRoom`
- **Alternating `batchKey`** (e.g. 5 cards vs 2) + **`debounce superseded`** → requests never settle; UI stuck on analyzing
- **`batch failed`** with **`invalid start`** / **`}` is invalid`** → assistant content not clean JSON (prose prefix, truncation, bad quotes)
- **`overlay shows failure`** → same error surfaced in UI; correlate with preceding `batch failed` line

Do not conclude “the code must be wrong” without checking whether the log shows HTTP success, parse failure, or batch thrash.
